laboratory_examinations.findings: Lower Thorax: Tiny bilateral pleural effusions. The lung bases are clear. Heart size normal. No pericardial effusion. Liver: Signal loss on out of phase sequence consistent with mild hepatic steatosis. The liver contours are smooth. No concerning solid or cystic lesions. Biliary: No intra- or extra-hepatic duct dilatation. The common bile duct is within normal limits. Gallbladder unremarkable. No cholelithiasis or choledocholithiasis. Pancreas: Fatty atrophy with mild edematous change in the neck and proximal body and peripancreatic standing. A 10 mm cystic lesion in the neck most consistent with a side-branch IPMN. No ductal abnormality. Spleen, adrenal glands, and kidneys are normal. No hydronephrosis or hydroureter. Gastrointestinal tract normal. No significant lymphadenopathy. No vascular abnormalities.
